commit.message: README.md: Archived

* Lock issues until a new maintainer (owner) comes.
* Remove 'my' TODOs and WIPs, those are not the project's progress now.

Xfce-notify-4.0: Revive missing rc file and directory in 3.94.

Oops, this was missed as well.
Gtk-2.0: Revive missing rc files in 3.94.0 source
Gitignore: Revert to 3.94.0 source
Configure.ac: Forgot to bump to 3.95.0
README.md: Update the header comment
Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [Chrome(ium)] Set unfocused tab label colors again
All: Revert to 3.94.0.149 source

Gnome-shell-3.24&3.26: [WorkspacePager] Switch to solid materials from OSDs

And drop debugging state test code.

Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [GtkButton] Set more finer sizing and placement for CSD titlebuttons

Anyway zero margin was incorrect.
Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [GtkScale] Refactor and clean up spacing

Configure.ac: Bump version to 3.95.0

Still some papercut issues are remained though.
Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [Budgie-desktop] Fix incorrect separator color and drop unneeded extend

Revert "Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [GtkComboBox] Set responsitve pop-up/down arrows in button.combo"

This reverts commit 665cd12455bc6debf550ff2d77576ae203d37474.
It's too difficult to cover all button cases currently, so revert this.

Gtk-3.2x&4.0: Decrease scaling_weight of Eta to 0.75

For some reasons in debugging, I've locked $sw as 0.8 in this development
cycle, but now it seems OK to apply more smaller weight...

Gtk-3.24&4.0: [GtkPathBar] Set child margins more precisely (2)

Hmm, margin property sometimes might not be applied in case the button node
had a child box container, so move baseline margin to padding property.

Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [Thunar] Tweak entry node height in the primary toolbar (3)

This 'should' fix the entry height finally... :/

Gtk-3.24&4.0: [GtkPathBar] Set child margins more precisely

We usually employ 'baseline' label margins for child labels, so do not
override top/bottom margins in childs elements.
Gtk-3.2x&4.0: Code cosmetics
README.md: Update comments for GtkSourceView color scheme

Extra: [GtkSourceView] Add experimental adapta-brila color scheme

I'm not sure that could make sense anyway.

README.md: Exclude 'Ubuntu' gnome-shell session from our supported desktops

Their sessions override user-themes in many places.
It's around time to say good-bye to Ubuntu. It means I'm OK to pin Ubuntu
as an unsupported distribution now.

Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [Gnome-recipe] Update styling more and more (3)

Ugghh, should not specify the parent containers anymore...
Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [Dconf-editor] Set version specific label margins

Gtk-2.0: [Pcmanfm] Update some styling (2)

* Handle width: 1px -> 4px.
* Use standard paned separator image.

Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [GtkHeaderBar] Set L/R border color for safety

Some apps enforce to embedding L/R borders via their stock CSSs, so let's
define L/R border color as well...
Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [Geary] Clean up left-overs

Gtk-3.2x&4.0: [Chrome(ium)] Improve more button border cases (2)
